The paper deals with deep learning methods for image analysis, specifically for event verification and image repurposing detection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of pre-trained networks and classifiers suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories, as it deals with analyzing images and their associated labels. Finally, the issue of image authenticity and manipulation may also place the paper in the cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-category.
